for men can have no more power over me, than what is given them from above. I am not in love with this passage through the Red Sea, for I have the weakness and infirmities of flesh and bloud plentifully in me; And I have prayed with my Saviour, Ut transir • t Calix iste, that this Cup of red wine might pass from me: but if not, Gods will (not mine) be done, and I shall most willing drink of this Cup as deep as he pleases, and enter in this Sea; yea, and pass through it in the way that he shall lead me.
